  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "Determining the most used word in any language, including Malayalam, can be challenging due to variations in context, usage, and regional dialects. However, common words that frequently appear in everyday conversation include:\n\n- \"\u0d05\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\" (alla) - meaning \"no\" or \"not\"\n- \"\u0d06\u0d23\u0d4d\" (a\u1e47u) - meaning \"is\" or \"am\"\n- \"\u0d07\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\" (illa) - meaning \"not\" or \"there isn't\"\n- \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d\" (enthu) - meaning \"what\"\n- \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41\u0d02\" (ennum) - meaning \"always\"\n\nThese words are widely used in multiple contexts and could be considered among the most frequently used in Malayalam.",
